<br>
The flames I like to see are about events that happen *in the game*.  I don't come here to read about Israel or President Bush or what happened to you in school today or what your political views are.  I want to read about the guy who wouldn't rez you or the guild that killed Yelniak just as your guild was getting ready to pull.<br>
<br>
The posters I like are *people who still actively play the game*.  I don't want to hear from someone who gave up the game a year ago or a month ago.  If you gave up EQ because you found it boring or because you didn't have time any more, that's fine, I can respect that - but I won't respect your opinion about in-game events any more, becase you *don't play*.  As rapidly as things are changing, even your month-old perspective is out of date.<br>
<br>
And, finally, in this forum I want to hear from people who play on *Drinal*.  I don't care what happens on your PvP server or any other server.  Quite frankly it's boring.  If you want to come to this forum and post, you should have a toon on Drinal.<br>
<br>
I've heard it stated &quot;if it weren't for the people who post that don't play anymore, this forum wouldn't be half as interesting&quot;.  Mostly that's stated by people who themselves don't play - rationalizing their own postings, as it were.  Me, I disagree.  This forum would be much more interesting if it only contained flames about the game, made by people who play the game, and play it on Drinal.<br>
<br>
And yes, I appreciate the irony that this flame is itself not on a game-related subject.  I consider it a meta-flame - a flame about flames, and as such barely tolerable.  Feel free to flame my hypocrisy, though.  ^_^<br>
<br>
It would almost be better if we had two flame sections - one reserved for in-game discussions, one where you could flame about anything at all.  I've seen that on other boards and I think it works well.  That way the people who want to talk about Reaganomics can do so to their heart's content without drowning out the news about the latest training incident in Cobalt Scar.<br>
<br>
That's it, that's all I wanted to say.  Now, let loose the dogs of flameage, or something like that.<br>
 <p>-Richard<BR>
<BR>
Monual Lifegiver<BR>
High Priest of Rodcet Nife<BR>
