<br>
I've always been uncomfortable with hiding behind an alias.  One of the things I hate most about the Internet is that it makes everyone completely anonymous, and because of that, they can act out in the most despicable manner possible without fear of repercussion or damaging their real-life identity.<br>
<br>
I don't ever want to fall into that trap.  I want people to know that I, Richard Lawson, am the real-life person behind Monual Lifegiver.  That makes me responsible for the behavior of my toon and makes my real-life reputation held accountable for what I do in the game.<br>
<br>
That's a purely personal viewpoint and I don't necessarily encourage other people to adopt it - *I* don't have to fear being stalked.  But as long as I'm on the internet, I will never hide behind an alias - I will always be Richard Lawson, no matter what. <p>-Richard<BR>
