<br>
And I guess I don't mind *so* much that non-EQ issues are discussed here... it's just that it seems to be all anyone talks about lately.  All too often flames degenerate into retired characters flaming each other with the same old insults, or people saying something as inflammatory as possible just to get a rise out of folks and seeing a bunch of non-Drinal users respond.  The real flames about EQ issues on Drinal seem to be subsumed in a sea of off-topic lameness.<br>
<br>
I really don't mind off-topic posts so much - I actually enjoyed the /flame blackberries post.  But it seems that people forget that the *main* purpose of this board is Drinal rants.  Its main purpose is *not* to be a social gathering place for people who may or may not have anything to do with EQ or Drinal.<br>
<br>
To use one of your analogies... if I went to a sports bar and all anyone ever talked about there is politics, I might be entertained for a short while, but eventually I'd like to talk sports and would get discouraged when every attempt to talk about sports is drowned out by the same old &quot;Bush sucks!&quot; arguments.<br>
<br>
If you want to come with me to alt.politics, I'm more than willing... I actually enjoy talking politics.  I'm a left-leaning Democrat and enjoy taking on all debate.<br>
<br>
But this isn't alt.politics.  Let's talk less about Bush and more about how much CiH sucks - I enjoy those kind of arguments!  I still haven't forgiven Fattee for yelling &quot;RAGEFIRE POP!&quot; into the ragefire channel back  when that camp was a major pain.<br>
<br>
There, see?  I can do on-topic flames, too.  =) <p>-Richard<BR>
